.TH "drm_connector_init_with_ddc" 9 "drm_connector_init_with_ddc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_connector_init_with_ddc \- Init a preallocated connector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_connector_init_with_ddc
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_connector_funcs *funcs "  ","
.BI "int connector_type "  ","
.BI "struct i2c_adapter *ddc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "connector" 12
the connector to init
.IP "funcs" 12
callbacks for this connector
.IP "connector_type" 12
user visible type of the connector
.IP "ddc" 12
pointer to the associated ddc adapter
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initialises a preallocated connector. Connectors should be
subclassed as part of driver connector objects.

Ensures that the ddc field of the connector is correctly set.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, error code on failure.
